Part 1 - Read Quality Score Distributions

My Software - dist_qscore.py output plots

R1 is more consistant in quality score for both data sets. As expected, read quality dips at the beginning and ands of the reads. Overall, all reads are averaging over 30 in phred33 encoded Q-scores.

Note: these plots really show the same information, except the one on the right connects the dots in a way that is probably misleading since these represent independent observations.
